data.enText: to fall downwards, often hitting the ground several times, but usually without serious injury; to make sb/sth fall in this way
He slipped and tumbled down the stairs.
to fall suddenly and in a dramatic way
The scaffolding came tumbling down.

data.chText: 在上届奥林匹克运动会上世界纪录大幅下滑。
data.enText: World records tumbled at the last Olympics.
to fall rapidly in value or amount
The price of oil is still tumbling.

data.chText: 翻滚；打滚；翻腾；轻松地倒下
data.enText: to move or fall somewhere in a relaxed, uncontrolled, or noisy way

data.chText: 一群吵吵嚷嚷的孩子一窝蜂地下了公共汽车。
data.enText: A group of noisy children tumbled out of the bus.

data.chText: 厚厚的金色鬈发垂在她的肩上。
data.enText: Thick golden curls tumbled down over her shoulders.

data.chText: 表演杂技；翻跟头；（尤指）做空翻动作
data.enText: to perform acrobatics on the floor, especially somersaults (= a jump in which you turn over completely in the air)
tumble to sth
to suddenly understand sth or be aware of sth
a sudden fall

data.chText: 骑师在第三道栅栏处给重重摔下马来。
data.enText: The jockey took a nasty tumble at the third fence.

data.chText: 合并消息传出，股价随即暴跌。
data.enText: Share prices took a sharp tumble following news of the merger.

data.chText: 混乱的一堆；杂乱不堪的一团

a tumble of blond curls

tr: a sudden drop from an upright position
example: he had a nasty spill on the ice

tr: an acrobatic feat of rolling or turning end over end
do gymnastics, roll and turn skillfully
suffer a sudden downfall, overthrow, or defeat
put clothes in a tumbling barrel, where they are whirled about in hot air, usually with the purpose of drying
example: Wash in warm water and tumble dry
Prices tumbled after the devaluation of the currency

tr: understand, usually after some initial difficulty
example: She didn't know what her classmates were plotting but finally caught on

tr: throw together in a confused mass
example: They tumbled the teams with no apparent pattern

tr: roll over and over, back and forth

example: The tower of the World Trade Center tumbled after the plane hit it
the building crumbled after the explosion
The clothes tumbled in the dryer
rising smoke whirled in the air

tr: cause to topple or tumble by pushing

value.def: If someone or something tumbles somewhere, they fall there with a rolling or bouncing movement.

example.ex: A small boy tumbled off a third floor fire escape...
example.tran: 一个小男孩从3楼防火梯上摔了下来。

example.ex: The dog had tumbled down the cliff…
He fell to the ground, and the gun tumbled out of his hand.
example.tran: 他跌到地上，枪从手里摔了出去。

example.ex: He injured his ribs in a tumble from his horse.
example.tran: 他从马背上摔下来时伤到了肋骨。

value.tran: 滚下;摔倒;跌落;翻滚而下

value.def: If prices or levels of something are tumbling, they are decreasing rapidly.

example.ex: House prices have tumbled by almost 30 per cent in real terms since mid-1989...
example.tran: 房价自 1989 年中期以来实际上暴跌了近 30%。

example.ex: Share prices continued to tumble today on the Tokyo stock market.
example.tran: 东京股市的股价今天继续暴跌。
急剧下降的通货膨胀率

example.ex: Oil prices took a tumble yesterday.

value.def: If water tumbles, it flows quickly over an uneven surface.

example.ex: Waterfalls crash and tumble over rocks.
example.tran: 瀑布飞流直溅，冲刷着岩石。

example.ex: ...the aromatic pines and tumbling streams of the Zonba Plateau.
example.tran: 松巴高原芬芳的松树与湍急的河流

value.def: If you say that someone tumbles into a situation or place, you mean that they get into it without being fully in control of themselves or knowing what they are doing.

example.ex: Many mothers and children tumble into poverty after divorce...
example.tran: 很多母亲和孩子在离婚后陷入贫困。

example.ex: There's no thought more pleasing than the prospect of tumbling into my apartment and slamming the door.
example.tran: 没有比一头冲进自己的公寓摔上房门更让我开心的事了。

value.tran: 突然闯入（某地）;陷入，浑然不觉地进入(某种状态)
